  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>RepairQ\u2019s import process allows users to batch-add or update records efficiently, enhancing data management and reducing manual entry. Users with Admin, Manager, or Inventory Manager roles can use built-in import templates to manage records like Tickets, Customers, Purchase Orders, and Inventory, with specific required values for each category.</p><p>We've recently improved system performance by moving the import process to an asynchronous queue. This change allows large file uploads to run in the background, preventing delays and browser timeouts caused by processing-heavy actions, ensuring a smoother experience. The asynchronous process eliminates database bottlenecks by queuing long-running tasks, and notifying users when these processes are complete.</p><h3 id=\"DataImportTaskQueue-ImportRules\">Import Rules</h3><p><strong>Column Matching</strong> - Columns are matched by header name. We recommend using the header names provided in our templates to ensure a successful import of the column values. Any columns added outside the provided template will be ignored.</p><p><strong>Required Values</strong> - Required values differ based on the import, such as tickets, customers, purchase orders, etc. Refer to the specific import guidelines for each category to ensure all necessary fields are included.</p><p><strong>Import Updates </strong>- If a line in the import file matches an existing record in RepairQ, the item will be updated with the data from your spreadsheet. Matches are made in the following order: SKU, Supplier SKU, and Name.</p><p><strong>Accepted File Formats</strong> - RepairQ accepts Excel (.xlsx), Comma-Separated Values (.csv), and Tab-Separated Values (.txt). We recommend using .xlsx files for the best upload experience.</p><h3 id=\"DataImportTaskQueue-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1933377786\" rel=\"nofollow\">RepairQ Data Import Resources</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Technical - 124a6d.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2734981154/Technical%20-%20124a6d.png?api=v2\"></span><p>After importing a large file, you will receive a notification confirming that the import action has been registered, and the file is now queued for processing. You can safely navigate away from the page, as the import will continue to process in the background.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Import 1.png\" width=\"443\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2734981154/Import%201.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"DataImportTaskQueue-ViewtheImportTaskQueue\">View the Import Task Queue</h2><p>On the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Reports </strong>\u2192 <strong>Queued Tasks</strong>. The <strong>Task Queue</strong> displays detailed information about the import, including the current status of the upload, the user who initiated the import, and the timestamp of the submission.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Import Queue.png\" width=\"578\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2734981154/Import%20Queue.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Import 2.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2734981154/Import%202.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"DataImportTaskQueue-ImportNotifications\">Import Notifications</h2><p>Once the import is completed, the user who submitted the import will receive an email with the subject <strong>&quot;Notification of Completed Tasks&quot;</strong>. This email includes a link to the page where the import was submitted, as well as a link to our Support page in case any issues arise.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Import 4.png\" width=\"753\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2734981154/Import%204.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.21.X</p>",
